Multithreading: Theory, Programs, and Interview Questions

Multithreading is a very important topic in Java, C#, Python, and system programming interviews.

What is Multithreading?

Multithreading is the process of executing multiple threads simultaneously within a single process.

A thread is the smallest unit of execution in a program.

Example

A web browser can:

Download files
Play music
Load web pages
Respond to user clicks

all at the same time using multiple threads.

Process vs Thread
Process	Thread
Independent program	Part of a process
Heavyweight	Lightweight
Separate memory	Shared memory
More resource usage	Less resource usage
Slow creation	Fast creation
Advantages of Multithreading
Better CPU utilization
Faster execution
Improved responsiveness
