Deadlock

Occurs when two or more threads wait indefinitely for each other.

Example:

Thread1 → Lock A → Waiting for Lock B

Thread2 → Lock B → Waiting for Lock A

Result:

Deadlock
Race Condition

Occurs when multiple threads modify shared data simultaneously.

Example:

count++;

This is not an atomic operation.

Thread Pool (Executor Framework)

Instead of creating threads repeatedly:

ExecutorService service =
    Executors.newFixedThreadPool(3);

Submit tasks:

service.submit(() ->
{
    System.out.println("Task Running");
});

Shutdown:

service.shutdown();
